   <body>
      <context>The Meeting Scheduler feature enables you to create Zoom meetings in <ph href="../../../Warehouse/Product_Name_Warehouse.xml#reference-9043/product_name"/>. <ph product="Include_in_Emp_PG">The Zoom authorization is performed as part of project collaboration. For more details refer to <i>Training Manual - Mind Build (Part 03)</i>
         </ph>
         <ph product="Exclude_PG_Content">For information in Meeting Scheduler, refer to<xref href="../../Project_Management/Collaboration/Meeting_Scheduler/MeetSch.xml">Meeting Scheduler</xref>.</ph>
      </context>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <p>In the module menu, click<uicontrol>Administration</uicontrol>. </p>
            <p> The<uicontrol>ADMINISTRATION</uicontrol> page is displayed. </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>In the navigation pane, expand<uicontrol>Functional Configurations</uicontrol>, and thenclick<uicontrol>Meeting Settings</uicontrol>. </p>
            <p>The<uicontrol>MEETING SETTINGS</uicontrol>page is displayed. </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>By default, the<uicontrol>Enable Zoom Meeting Scheduler</uicontrol>check box is selected thatindicates the Meeting Scheduler feature is enabled in the application.</p>
            <p>To turn off theMeeting Scheduler feature, clear the check box. </p>
         </li>
      </ol>
